cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper discusses methods for improving low-resource neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses machine learning techniques such as transfer learning, semi-supervised and unsupervised learning, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of monolingual data, which can be processed using computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
